[1
Date: 12 Jul 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, 11 Jul 2001 [edited

ROME -- Italy's 17th case of "mad cow" disease, or bovine spongiform
encephalopathy (BSE), was confirmed by the national institute for
research into spongiform encephalopathies in Turin. The animal
concerned was 14 years old and discovered in Aosta in the north.
A total of 17 BSE cases have been detected in Italy since it launched
its testing program for the fatal brain-wasting disease in January, in
compliance with European Union regulations.
All animals over 30 months old now have to be tested. So far, over 100
000 tests have been carried out.
­­
